  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-ceat.200600266.pdf_2_5",
    "text": "2.1 Experimental Setup",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.07170542852337189,
      0.29786706353806963,
      0.24612403129574947,
      0.31104651098083586
    ],
    "page": "docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-ceat.200600266.pdf_2",
    "order": 10
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-ceat.200600266.pdf_2_36",
    "text": "Sewage water was taken from a septic tank at residential building No. 2 situated in the northern part of a university in Wuhan, China. The water quality is shown in Tab. 1.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.496124027047892,
      0.3095238094696039,
      0.8837209217694574,
      0.35029069739172025
    ],
    "page": "docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-ceat.200600266.pdf_2",
    "order": 11
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-ceat.200600266.pdf_2_6",
    "text": "The reactor was made of plastic with dimensions of 40 × 30 × 42 cm. The effective volume was 40.5 L. The reactor was partitioned into two compartments by a clapboard, with one compartment twice the size of the other. A tubular aerator was fitted at the top of the pool level so that aerobic and anoxic biofilms could be formed in the upper and lower parts, respectively. The hollow fiber membrane assembly was fitted in the other pool. A small perforated pipe aerator was fitted under the membrane assembly. The clapboard height was lower than the waterline to ensure water flowed from the bigger compartment into the smaller, so that membrane fouling could be alleviated. The bioreactor is shown in Fig. 1.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.06976744157116847,
      0.3240709121655181,
      0.4555992500252337,
      0.48983134922501814
    ],
    "page": "docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-ceat.200600266.pdf_2",
    "order": 12
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-ceat.200600266.pdf_2_37",
