  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_docstructbench_llm-raw-scihub-o.O-ceat.200600266.pdf_2_43",
    "text": "It can be seen from Fig. 2, curve (b) that the membrane flux increases immediately after the application of an electric pulse. The rate of reduction of the average membrane flux is lower than that found with no electric field. This suggests that the application of pulsed electric field in MBRs is an effective method for resisting the deposition of particles on the membrane surface, cleaning the filter cake, and reducing membrane",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.4980620187832847,
      0.8066860467229843,
      0.8837209289230176,
      0.9011627905589926
